O diute, the one night, O doth all the earth live, O diute, O diute, give health and health.
Where the heart would, where the nerve of mania, O diute, the one night, O diute, give health and health.
O come, O be faithful, joyful and triumphant, O come ye, O come ye to bless the world.
Come and behold him, O'er the King of Angels, O come, let us adore him, O come, let us adore him, O come, let us adore him, Christ the Lord.
Sing, choirs of angels, sing in exultation, Sing, all ye citizens of heaven above.
Glory to God, glory in the highest, O come, let us adore him, O come, let us adore him, O come, let us adore him, Christ the Lord.
Amen.
